1
00:00:05,891 --> 00:00:09,923
And look, you say
‘calling for Kṛṣṇa’.

2
00:00:10,465 --> 00:00:12,743
That’s not something
in the past.

3
00:00:12,743 --> 00:00:17,016
[Krishna Will Protect Me!]

4
00:00:17,441 --> 00:00:19,482
And if you look
to Kṛṣṇa līla,

5
00:00:19,482 --> 00:00:25,741
what would be expected
from progressive servitors?

6
00:00:25,964 --> 00:00:30,707
We hear in the case 
of Draupadī,

7
00:00:30,707 --> 00:00:37,149
that when she’s …
this is līla, pastimes, Mahābhārata .

8
00:00:37,149 --> 00:00:40,565
But when she is lost,
 

9
00:00:40,565 --> 00:00:45,605
she’s gambled away
by her husbands.

10
00:00:47,275 --> 00:01:06,226
And when the Kauravas
want to humiliate her

11
00:01:06,226 --> 00:01:11,907
and humiliate the Pāṇḍavas, 
and they call for her,

12
00:01:13,156 --> 00:01:18,211
to enter the assemble,
and they want to strip her, publicly,

13
00:01:18,211 --> 00:01:22,528
to disrobe her
in front of an open assemble.

14
00:01:22,528 --> 00:01:27,718
This woman of impeccable character,
saintly qualities, and dignity.

15
00:01:27,718 --> 00:01:32,671
They want to disrobe her publicly—
now that they own her.
 

16
00:01:35,111 --> 00:01:37,307
And when she enters 
that scene …

17
00:01:37,307 --> 00:01:38,760
What are we told first?

18
00:01:38,760 --> 00:01:42,850
—She’s crying, 
she’s calling for Kṛṣṇa.

19
00:01:42,850 --> 00:01:46,010
And there is no response.

20
00:01:47,747 --> 00:01:58,842
And she’s trying
to keep her dignity, modesty.

21
00:01:58,874 --> 00:02:01,600
And at the end, 
when she has …
 

22
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:04,026
she’s holding with her hands
her remaining cloth,

23
00:02:04,026 --> 00:02:09,706
and when she is 
utterly hopeless, and helpless,

24
00:02:09,706 --> 00:02:13,484
she throws up both
of her hands in the air.

25
00:02:13,619 --> 00:02:16,340
She surrenders to her destiny, 
her fate,

26
00:02:16,340 --> 00:02:20,621
and she says,
“Hey, Gopī-jana-vallabha!”

27
00:02:20,623 --> 00:02:28,793
When she addresses Kṛṣṇa
as the beloved of the Vraja‒gopīs,

28
00:02:28,793 --> 00:02:31,355
then Kṛṣṇa comes.

29
00:02:32,455 --> 00:02:36,486
But He didn’t respond 
before that.

30
00:02:36,606 --> 00:02:39,576
Because mām ekaṁ śaraṇaṁ vraja
[Bg: 18.66]

31
00:02:39,576 --> 00:02:44,716
vraja śaraṇaṁ—
this type of total

32
00:02:44,716 --> 00:02:52,332
giving off the self over to Kṛṣṇa, 
and one’s fate to Kṛṣṇa.

33
00:02:56,890 --> 00:03:00,991
ānukūlyasya saṅkalpaḥ
prātikūlyasya varjanam

34
00:03:00,991 --> 00:03:05,811
rakṣiṣyatīti viśvāso
goptṛtve … [Cc: 2.22.100]

35
00:03:05,811 --> 00:03:10,064
Offering oneself to Kṛṣṇa,
expecting “Kṛṣṇa will protect me.”

36
00:03:10,064 --> 00:03:14,332
Rākhe kṛṣṇa mare ke, mare kṛṣṇa rākhe ke
[from Swāmī Prabhupād’s lectures]

37
00:03:14,332 --> 00:03:17,158
If Kṛṣṇa wants to protect me—
no one can harm me,

38
00:03:17,158 --> 00:03:20,044
If He wants to kill me—
no one can save me.

39
00:03:20,044 --> 00:03:25,633
When she reaches
that level, the vraja śaraṇaṁ,

40
00:03:25,633 --> 00:03:27,425
“Hey, Gopī-jana-vallabha!”

41
00:03:27,425 --> 00:03:36,096
Then Kṛṣṇa is miraculously,
mysteriously supplying the cloth.

42
00:03:36,116 --> 00:03:40,066
And we hear, what is that?
—When she was a girl,

43
00:03:40,066 --> 00:03:44,960
and Kṛṣṇa cut once,
and she tore her cloth

44
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:49,130
and made a bandage 
for Kṛṣṇa.

45
00:03:49,350 --> 00:03:57,032
You give little finite to Kṛṣṇa,
and the infinite comes in return.

